commits.message:
Auth setup commit

Was doing this really late and got some messy commits, squashing to make clearer what is happening where

This commit makes functions for refreshing token as well as a function for a safe API call (this was recommended by Anthony). It also sets up the saving of tokens from verification calls, and makes a class of error for authorization

Merge pull request #128 from seehorne/main

Merge all of Budhil's work into the auth branch

add logout

this is based on michael's button, but i used the user defaults thing budhil had to make the state change persistent. also made sure to call it when we log in. this is a quality of life commit mostly
Make failed auth change you to logged out, successful verify to logged in

Set up put calls for notification and favorite changes

Not fully implemented, more of a placeholder to set up the call, need to figure out how to actually make the array

Possible way to get favorite events put call parameterized

Doesn't seem to be totally there yet, but bookmarking here

Call auth functions, make it structurally possible to do so

I should have made this smaller commits, but this removes async from the auth handling, which conflicts with callback functions. It also makes notification bool not transient so it can actually save.

remove duplicate completion handling

maybe trying to handle the same completion twice is what makes it not seem to run at all?

change getFavorites to GET request

typo, had it as put

Restore "duplicate" handling but reposition it

Turns out I needed that handling but the problem was it was in the 403 block when it shouldnt have been, so nothing ever happened if the code was good
Make token say bearer exactly once
Update body so favorites and notifs can be passed

Disentangle how favorites and notifs are written

They were overwriting each other, lets have them not do that by having the heart button change only favorites and the bell button change only notifications
try to save the db favorites to local
